</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF7EFF34A7ADFAD0FDF7DA21" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADFAD0FEF0D958" blockId="231.[189,310,1343,1369]" box="[189,310,1343,1369]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF7EFF34A7ADFAD0FEF0D958" bold="true" box="[189,310,1343,1369]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7ADFAD0FEF0D958" bold="true" box="[189,310,1343,1369]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADFA9FFDF7DA21" blockId="231.[188,1399,1392,1568]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A7ADFA9FFE86D98B" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,320,1392,1418]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7ADFA9FFE86D98B" box="[189,320,1392,1418]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from the other two genera of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A4B3FA9FFBE2D98B" authorityName="Quintero" authorityYear="1986" box="[931,1060,1392,1418]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Charinidae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a straight carina anterior to the lateral eyes (
<figureCitation id="9FD1BEE6FF7EFF34A578FA79FD21D9B0" box="[616,743,1430,1457]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="406.[189,232,1925,1951]" captionTargetBox="[253,1331,265,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-45@406.[253,1334,265,1898]" captionTargetPageId="406" captionText="Fig. 151. Weygoldtia consonensis sp. nov. (AMNH), general morphology, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A–B, E–F = 1 mm; C–D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5536833/files/figure.png" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Fig. 151A</figureCitation>
), as well as the following combination of characters: tritosternum projected anteriorly with pair of prominent setae near anterior pair of setae; pedipalp tarsus with one or two setae at base of ventral row of cleaning organ; leg IV distitibia with seven to nine trichobothria in 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A66AF9E8FE54DA21" box="[378,402,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">sc</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A6DBF9E9FE19DA21" box="[459,479,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">sf</emphasis>
series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF7EFF34A7ADF9A5FE95DAB8" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADF9A5FE82DA65" blockId="231.[189,324,1610,1636]" box="[189,324,1610,1636]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF7EFF34A7ADF9A5FE82DA65" bold="true" box="[189,324,1610,1636]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7ADF9A5FE82DA65" bold="true" box="[189,324,1610,1636]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADF994FE95DAB8" blockId="231.[189,1399,1658,1721]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
Patronym honoring Dr Peter Weygoldt for his contributions to arachnology in general and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A3E1F995FAB1DA95" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1883" box="[1265,1399,1658,1684]" class="Arachnida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Amblypygi</taxonomicName>
in particular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF7EFF3BA7ADF90CFC78DE43" lastPageId="232" lastPageNumber="233" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADF90CFEE9DAFC" blockId="231.[189,303,1763,1789]" box="[189,303,1763,1789]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF7EFF34A7ADF90CFEE9DAFC" bold="true" box="[189,303,1763,1789]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7ADF90CFEE9DAFC" bold="true" box="[189,303,1763,1789]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADF8FBFD4BDBE9" blockId="231.[188,1399,1812,2024]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
The number of articles on the tibia and tarsus of leg I in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A46DF8FBFBC6DB2F" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[893,1024,1812,1838]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A46DF8FBFBC6DB2F" box="[893,1024,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that in species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A7ADF8D6FEEADB52" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1889" box="[189,300,1849,1875]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Catageus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7ADF8D6FEEADB52" box="[189,300,1849,1875]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Catageus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the two genera may be distinguished by the dorsal spines on the pedipalp trochanter of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A7AFF8B0FEEADB78" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1889" box="[191,300,1887,1913]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Catageus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7AFF8B0FEEADB78" box="[191,300,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Catageus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A528F8B1FD7DDB79" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[568,699,1886,1912]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A528F8B1FD7DDB79" box="[568,699,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the different numbers of trichobothria in the frontal and caudal rows of the distitibia in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A534F86BFD55DB9F" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1889" box="[548,659,1924,1950]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Catageus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A534F86BFD55DB9F" box="[548,659,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Catageus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are equal in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A46DF86BFBC6DB9F" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[893,1024,1924,1950]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A46DF86BFBC6DB9F" box="[893,1024,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the absence of a straight carina anterior to the lateral eyes, a synapomorphy of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A5E1F846FCB5DBC2" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[753,883,1961,1987]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A5E1F846FCB5DBC2" box="[753,883,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and spines between dorsal spine 1 and the proximal margin of the pedipalp femur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF71FF3BA7ADFEE6FE5ADDFF" blockId="232.[187,1400,265,511]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF71FF3BA7ADFEE6FE86DD22" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,320,265,291]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA7ADFEE6FE86DD22" box="[189,320,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the family 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF71FF3BA52EFEE6FD79DD22" authorityName="Quintero" authorityYear="1986" box="[574,703,265,291]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Charinidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF71FF3BA5DCFEE6FC73DD22" author="Miranda G. S. &amp; Giupponi A. P. &amp; Scharff N. &amp; Prendini L." box="[716,949,265,292]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Miranda" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" refId="ref151478" refString="Miranda G. S., Giupponi A. P., Scharff N. &amp; Prendini L. 2021. Phylogeny and biogeography of the pantropical whip spider family Charinidae (Arachnida: Amblypygi). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zlaa 101" title="Phylogeny and biogeography of the pantropical whip spider family Charinidae (Arachnida: Amblypygi)" type="book" year="2021">
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FF71FF3BA5DCFEE6FCF7DD22" box="[716,817,265,291]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Miranda</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA426FEE5FCAFDD22" box="[822,873,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
), not 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF71FF3BA4E2FEE6FB42DD22" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1010,1156,265,291]" class="Arachnida" family="Charontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Charontidae</taxonomicName>
, due to the following characters: spines absent on pedipalp trochanter; small dorsal spines and ventral spines absent from pedipalp tibia; pedipalp tibia with two dorsal spines, distal spine longer than proximal, instead of one long spine proximally, with small spine close to its base, followed by smaller spines; pedipalp tibia ventral spine situated distally, near distal margin of tibia, instead of proximally; only one seta, instead of several, at base of cleaning organ on pedipalp tarsus; equal number of trichobothria in 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA3D9FE2EFB27DDDB" box="[1225,1249,449,474]" italics="true" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">sc</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA209FE2FFAEBDDDB" box="[1305,1325,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">sf</emphasis>
series of leg IV distitibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF71FF3BA7ADFDC8FC78DE43" blockId="232.[189,958,550,578]" box="[189,958,550,578]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA7ADFDC8FC84DE40" bold="true" box="[189,834,550,577]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
Key to the identification of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF71FF3BA5ADFDC9FC84DE40" authorityName="Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2018" box="[701,834,550,577]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Weygoldtia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA5ADFDC9FC84DE40" bold="true" box="[701,834,550,577]" italics="true" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Weygoldtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="9FD1BEE6FF71FF3BA442FDC8FC70DE43" box="[850,950,551,578]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="405.[189,232,1225,1251]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1189]" captionTargetId="figure-21@405.[189,1399,265,1189]" captionTargetPageId="405" captionText="Fig. 150. Map plotting known distributions of species of Weygoldtia Miranda, Giupponi, Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2018 in Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5536829/files/figure.png" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF71FF3BA7ADFDB8FAB1DF29" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" type="key">
<keyStep id="BC1EBAC6FF71FF3BA7ADFDB8FAB1DF29" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
<key id="737BF552FF71FF3BA7ADFDB8FAB1DF29" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
