<emphasis id="359E7E71FF71FF3BA42AFCE2FB9CDF29" bold="true" box="[826,1114,781,808]" italics="true" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Weygoldtia consonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF71FF3BA371FCE1FB7DDF29" box="[1121,1211,782,808]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="9FD1BEE6FF71FF3BA3DBFCE1FAA8DF29" box="[1227,1390,781,808]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="406.[189,232,1925,1951]" captionStartId-1="407.[189,232,1631,1657]" captionStartId-2="408.[189,232,1047,1073]" captionTargetBox-0="[253,1331,265,1898]" captionTargetBox-1="[189,1399,265,1594]" captionTargetBox-2="[189,1398,265,1002]" captionTargetId-0="figure-45@406.[253,1334,265,1898]" captionTargetId-1="figure-35@407.[189,1399,265,1595]" captionTargetId-2="figure-27@408.[189,1399,265,1002]" captionTargetPageId-0="406" captionTargetPageId-1="407" captionTargetPageId-2="408" captionText-0="Fig. 151. Weygoldtia consonensis sp. nov. (AMNH), general morphology, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A–B, E–F = 1 mm; C–D = 0.5 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 152. Weygoldtia consonensis sp. nov. (AMNH), male gonopod. A. Ventral view. B. Posterior view. C. Dorsal view. D. Sinistral side of gonopod. E. Dorsal lobe. F. Processus internus." captionText-2="Fig. 153. Weygoldtia consonensis sp. nov. (AMNH), antenniform leg I, ♂. A. Apex of leg, lateral view. B. Modified claw, rod sensilla and tarsal organ." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536833" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536835" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536841" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5536833/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5536835/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5536841/files/figure.png" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Figs 151–153</figureCitation>
